ray-project/ray#56925.body:
### What happened + What you expected to happen

In the Jobs page, when filtering the Job List by entering Job ID/Submission ID, it was found that if there are entries with job_id as null or submission_id as null, even after clearing all filter criteria, the original entries cannot be fully displayed.

### Code Analysis
In the method changeFilter for setting filter criteria, after clearing `job_id/submission_id`, the filter array still retains the filter criteria `{ key: "job_id", val: "", key: "submission_id", val: "" }`, which filters out entries with null values, causing the inability to display all entries.

```
  const changeFilter = (
    key: "job_id" | "submission_id" | "status",
    val: string,
  ) => {
    const f = filter.find((e) => e.key === key);
    if (f) {
      f.val = val;
    } else {
      filter.push({ key, val });
    }
    setFilter([...filter]);

  };
```

